<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="first-n">first <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /fɜːst/    美 /fɜːrst/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>开始；开端；(月的) 第一日：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the first of May / May (the) first 
5月1日</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Things went wrong <strong>from the (very) first</strong>.
事情从一开始就出了差错。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>第一个人 / 事物：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is always <strong>the first</strong> to come and the last to leave.
他总是第一个来最后一个走。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>firstly /'fɜːstli/ adv [句子副词]  </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The plum trees are<strong><em>_</em></strong>__first to flower even as the snow is melting.  （2020全国）  </li>
<li>At the first, I thought I knew everything and could make decisions by myself.  （2016 全国改 改错）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. the  2. 去掉 the  </p></div>